/span></a>Removing <code class=3D"inline-code" node=3D"[object Object]">@Co=
ntributesBinding.rank</code></h3>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/square/anvil/blob/main/annotations/src/mai=
n/java/com/squareup/anvil/annotations/ContributesBinding.kt#L117-L133">Anvi=
l's</a>
<code class=3D"inline-code" node=3D"[object Object]">@ContributesBinding</c=
ode> annotation has a <code class=3D"inline-code" node=3D"[object Object]">=
rank</code> parameter that can automatically deduplicate
contributions for the same binding. This is helpful when Gradle modules don=
't depend on each other
and therefore cannot use the strongly typed <code class=3D"inline-code" nod=
e=3D"[object Object]">replaces</code> parameter. For example, we use this f=
eature
in device tests to replace real implementations with fakes.</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/ZacSweers/metro/blob/main/runtime/src/comm=
onMain/kotlin/dev/zacsweers/metro/ContributesBinding.kt">Metro's</a>
<code class=3D"inline-code" node=3D"[object Object]">@ContributesBinding</c=
ode> annotation doesn't support <code class=3D"inline-code" node=3D"[object=
 Object]">rank</code>, so we had to migrate hundreds of usages.
Our <a href=3D"https://ralf-wondratschek.com/presentation/android-at-scale-=
at-square.html">Gradle module structure</a>
enforces dependency inversion, which means implementation modules aren't al=
lowed to depend on other
implementation modules. As a result, they can't use <code class=3D"inline-c=
ode" node=3D"[object Object]">replaces</code> to reference the implementati=
on
they supersede.</p>
